</div>I haven't been to a Wal-mart in a while, but I don't remember them selling handguns. Mainly just rifles and shotguns in the sporting goods section.<br />
<br />
If you think of it only as a weapon to kill humans, I suppose it would seem very odd. But growing up in the rural South I associate those two firearms with hunting and as a sport. I used to do archery, and enjoyed mastering the skill of improving my aim at targets, even though I never used it to hunt and certainly never considered shooting a person with a bow and arrow. Also used to enjoy target practice with rifles, though again I never hunted with one - though I did go bird hunting with a shotgun on a few occasions.<br />
<br />
Different cultures, I guess. I've heard that in one country they sell coffins in the grocery stores.</div>
