</div>Trust me it seems like that to those of us on the inside too. <br />
<br />
When it seems like one side isn't even willing to come to the table with alternate solutions, because as far as they seem to be concerned anyone who says they want gun control wants to outright ban all firearms. <br />
<br />
We cut funding to mental health facilities. We stigmatize those who seek mental healthcare. <br />
<br />
We have people who want to arm teachers.<br />
<br />
We have people who want to post armed guards outside of all our schools. <br />
<br />
We do actually have people who want to ban all guns. (Dumb)<br />
<br />
On the other hand we have people who think any gun law is a major restriction on their lives. (Dumber)<br />
<br />
It's a majorly ****ed up situation, with no easy solutions, and nobody is going to be happy about the outcome.</div>
