</div>To clarify, &quot;mental illness&quot; is a medical term.  &quot;Insanity&quot; is a legal term.  They have two separate definitions, but are not mutually exclusive.  In this case the person would be considered &quot;Guilty but Mentally Ill&quot;.<br />
