    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_533568">How would the colonists have overthrown British rule without firearms*?<br />
<br />
I'm not trying to go vigilante seditionist here, but I'm genuinely asking - do we still have the right to throw off tyrannical government (which I am neither saying nor implying that ours is) with lethal force, or is that something man has now evolved beyond? Did the founding fathers intend to safeguard the freedom of our nation against potential tyranny by ensuring the armament of its citizens?<br />
<br />
And even if so, is there a since-realized greater good which now prevails/should prevail over those original intentions?<br />
<br />
*Or does this not even apply as (for the most part) we no longer have volunteer militias?<br />
<br />
<b>Please ignore this comment if you consider it sarcastic or if you just have a snide retort - I'm asking legitimately.</b></div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
